📄 IBM COS – Deleting / Updating Lifecycle Policies

🔎 Overview

In IBM Cloud Object Storage (COS), lifecycle configuration is handled as a single policy document per bucket.

👉 Important:

* You cannot delete a single rule directly
* You must update the entire lifecycle configuration
* Or remove it completely

⸻

🧠 Key Principle

Lifecycle = 1 configuration JSON per bucket

So:

* Modify rule → update full config
* Delete rule → remove it from JSON and reapply
* Delete all rules → delete lifecycle configuration

⸻

🗑️ Option 1 — Delete Entire Lifecycle Policy

Using AWS CLI (recommended)

aws s3api delete-bucket-lifecycle \
  --bucket BUCKET_NAME \
  --endpoint-url https://s3.REGION.cloud-object-storage.appdomain.cloud

👉 Result:

* All lifecycle rules are removed
* Bucket no longer has any automatic cleanup

⸻

✏️ Option 2 — Remove a Specific Rule

Step 1: Get current lifecycle config

aws s3api get-bucket-lifecycle-configuration \
  --bucket BUCKET_NAME \
  --endpoint-url https://s3.REGION.cloud-object-storage.appdomain.cloud

⸻

Step 2: Edit JSON

Remove the rule you don’t want.

Example:

Before:

{
  "Rules": [
    {
      "ID": "delete-after-30-days",
      "Status": "Enabled",
      "Expiration": { "Days": 30 }
    },
    {
      "ID": "cleanup-multipart",
      "Status": "Enabled",
      "AbortIncompleteMultipartUpload": {
        "DaysAfterInitiation": 1
      }
    }
  ]
}

After (remove multipart rule):

{
  "Rules": [
    {
      "ID": "delete-after-30-days",
      "Status": "Enabled",
      "Expiration": { "Days": 30 }
    }
  ]
}

⸻

Step 3: Apply updated config

aws s3api put-bucket-lifecycle-configuration \
  --bucket BUCKET_NAME \
  --lifecycle-configuration file://lifecycle.json \
  --endpoint-url https://s3.REGION.cloud-object-storage.appdomain.cloud

⸻

⚠️ Important Considerations

1. ❗ No Partial Delete API

* No command like “delete rule X”
* Always full overwrite

⸻

2. ⚠️ Overwrite Risk

* put-bucket-lifecycle-configuration replaces everything
* If you forget a rule → it is deleted

👉 Always:

* backup config before editing

⸻

3. ⏱️ Effect is Not Immediate

* Lifecycle engine runs asynchronously
* Changes may take time to apply

⸻

4. 🔄 Existing Objects Are Not Reverted

* If objects were already deleted → irreversible
* Removing a rule does NOT restore anything

⸻

5. 🧪 Safe Approach

Best practice:

1. get config
2. modify locally
3. reapply
4. verify

⸻

🔍 Verification

aws s3api get-bucket-lifecycle-configuration \
  --bucket BUCKET_NAME \
  --endpoint-url https://s3.REGION.cloud-object-storage.appdomain.cloud

⸻

🚨 Common Pitfalls

* ❌ Forgetting other rules when updating → accidental deletion
* ❌ Wrong endpoint/region → config applied to wrong bucket or fails
* ❌ Assuming rule deletion is immediate
* ❌ Not backing up original config

⸻

🧠 Summary

* Lifecycle config = single JSON document
* No per-rule delete → must update or remove full config
* Use:
    * delete-bucket-lifecycle → remove all
    * put-bucket-lifecycle-configuration → update rules

